         I like the change, but, this does not "balance us".  As others have pointed out, there are a lot of areas Pets are not allowed because of pathing and what not.  This change does nothing to increase our effectiveness in those encounters and does nothing to address our biggest problems on raids, that adding necros to High End encounters has diminishing returns.  We are not talking about killing Woushi here.  She doesn't live long enough for any dot's to run full course.  </P><P>We need help in battles that last 5 minutes or more, where all of our dots, if allowed to be used by multiple nec's, would have a nice impact on the speed in which the mob dies.  It's is hard enough in a lot of these encounters finding 1 or 2 dots that land, but when you have to divide those that do up amongst the different nec's on the raid, it is frustrating to say the least.</P><P>I still like this change though.  I for one, if it goes live, will go play with Cavern Lotuses in FG more often in full resist gear to see how long my pet can last.  I'll play with other summoning magic casting mobs more as well.  But, it still doesn't address our biggest need:</P><P>Dot Stacking!</P><P>Wurtin<BR>59th lvl Defiler of E'ci</P><P>“All that is necessary for the triumph of evil is for good men to do nothing.” Edmund Burke<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
